String -
It's group of characters is called as string 

We have 3 types of predefined Classes for string
	1. String Class
	2. StringBuffer Class
	3. StringBuilder Class 
	
1) String Class -
			- It's Immutable / Unchangeable / Value can't change
			- Slow for modifications
			- Stored in String Pool
			- Thread-unsafe
			
2) StringBuffer Class -
			- Mutable object
			- Slow (synchronized)
			- Thread-safe
			- Good for multi-threading
			
			
3) StringBuilder Class - 
			- Mutable object
			- Fast (not synchronized)
			- Thread-unsafe
			- Good for single-threading
			 
				 